## tool-sysprompt-cfg: sysprompt_cfg tool definition

### sysprompt_cfg(action, model, file, content, newdir) -> str
Unified system prompt management tool.

**actions:**
- list_dir — list all system prompt directories
- list — list files in a model's prompt dir (requires model)
- read — read a prompt file or full assembled prompt (requires model; file optional)
- write — write/overwrite a prompt file (requires model, file, content)
- delete — delete a file or entire dir (requires model; file optional)
- copy_dir — copy prompt dir to new name (requires model, newdir)
- set_dir — assign prompt dir to model (requires model, newdir)

**model:** model key (e.g. 'samaritan') or 'self' for current model
**file:** section name (e.g. 'behavior') or full filename (e.g. '.system_prompt_behavior')
**content:** text to write (for action='write')
**newdir:** new directory name (for copy_dir/set_dir)

IMPORTANT: You MUST call this tool to make any system prompt change. Do NOT describe changes in text — execute the tool call.
